record_data.record_plain_text: FERC Electric Tariff Volume No. 5 Reactive Supply and Voltage Control From Generation Sources Service Wabash Valley Power Association, Inc. ("WVPA") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Prairie State Energy Campus facility ("Facility") located in the Ameren Illinois ("AMIL") zones in the Midwest Independent Transmission System Operator, Inc.'s ("Midwest ISO") transmission footprint. Wabash Valley owns an undivided 5.06 percent interest in the Facility. This rate schedule sets forth Wabash Valley's revenue requirements for its partial ownership interest for the provision of Reactive Supply Service from the Facility pursuant to the Reactive Power Revenue Requirements in Schedule 2 of the Midwest ISO's Open Access Transmission, Energy and Operating Reserves Markets Tariff. Wabash Valley's monthly revenue requirement consists of charges for the fixed capability component and does not include charges for any heating losses. REVENUE REQUIREMENT: Wabash Valley's revenue requirements for the Facility shall be calculated as follows: 5.06% of Prairie State Energy Campus Annual Revenue Requirement $223,092 Monthly Revenue Requirement $18,591 Effective Date: May 1, 2017
